    <h1><img src="../../images/e2e-viv-70x70-1.png" />E2E Audit</h1>
    <p>
        The audit of the internet election results is a significant improvement over auditing of in-person and
        mail-in processes.  Where in-person auditing requirements are minimal, mail-in requirements are complex
        if not impractical because ballot chain of custody requires following ballots through numerous hands in
        numerous uncontrolled locations.  It is impractical to follow a ballot through the mail service.  Even if each
        ballot were tracked, to the delivery address, the chain is custody is broken because there is no reliable method
        of ensuring that the registered voter actually received the ballot.  The ballot simply reappears when it is completed
        and returned to the poll location.  With internet voting, the digital trail of the ballot can remain unbroken.
    </p><p>
        The advantage of have duplicate databases hosted by the State, Republican and Democrat party is that each can conduct their
        own audit and the results can be corroborated.
    </p><p>
        The combination of the Blockchain Nonce, and the signature enables detection of signature records that are directly inserted into the
        signature and vote database tables.  It allows signatures and completed ballots that have been fraudulently inserted to be removed
        from the candidate count totals.  It allows for discovery of signatures submitted by the same device, it allows discovery of
        signatures submitted from the same location using an unusual number of different devices, it allows discovery of signatures where
        the same head shot is used.

